After adding a macro via the { shortcut it would be great if one could edit the macro to set its properties. Right now we have to click on the macro and select edit (or double-click). This interrupts the "keyboard only" workflow while typing text in the editor.

When trying to insert a macro with a parameter, e.g.
{attachments:patterns=.*pdf}
the "automatic" conversion of :p kicks in into a smiley, effectively denying to insert the wanted macro.
The result is something like
{attachments(smiley)atterns...}

Wanted behaviour: when inserting macros I don't want to have the smiley auto-conversion active.

Also tried with
  {attachments|pattern=.*pdf}
but this results in a new "wiki-markup"-block.

See attachment.

The only solution that seems to work always:
enter a colon, then a pipe, then the parameter:
{attachments:|pattern=.*pdf}

