When editing tables if you ever change the layout (like to a preset style *Heading 3*) you can never change it back to the css class *confluenceTd* that it had originally.

h3.Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a page with a table, enter some data in it
# Save the page, and notice that this is the td entry in the HTML source (the table content itself does not matter):
{code}
<td class="confluenceTd">asd</td>
{code}
# Edit the page again, this time, highlight "asd", and change the formatting to *Heading 3*.
# Save the page, notice that this is the td entry now (notice the h3 wrapping around the asd):
{code}
<td class="confluenceTd"><h3 id="sasdd-asd">asd</h3></td>
{code}
# Edit the page again, change the formatting back to *Paragraph*
# Save the page, notice that the td entry now has paragraph wrappings:
{code}
<td class="confluenceTd"><p>asd</p></td>
{code}

There is no possible way for us to change from:
{code}
<td class="confluenceTd"><h3 id="sasdd-asd">asd</h3></td>
{code}
Back to the original:
{code}
<td class="confluenceTd">asd</td>
{code}

This causes tables with uneven cells due to the different formatting for cells with the <p> tags, and cells without.

